  "unmapped_findings": [
    "Phosphorus substitution for Al in κ-carbide reduces cleavage stress by 45%, leading to severe embrittlement",
    "Misch metal (Ce/La) addition and argon stirring can mitigate P embrittlement by forming P-containing inclusions and removing AlN inclusions",
    "High Mn (>25%) steels are not suitable for conventional wrought steelmaking, production is limited to casting industry",
    "Hot rolled steels slow cooled after deformation have poor toughness due to SRO and κ-carbide precipitation, which can be recovered by solution treatment at 1100°C",
    "Grain refinement via hot rolling and recrystallization improves ductility of the alloy compared to cast counterparts at equivalent strength levels",
    "Si addition increases fluidity of molten steel and decreases melting point by 30°C per wt.% Si, improving castability"
  ]
